{
  "texts": [
    "The fractional stretch of the mF-ring allows for a measurement of image ellipticity which could originate from many possible features such as the shadow (Falcke et al. 2000; Cunningham & Bardeen 1973) or inner shadow (Chael et al. 2021).",
    "However, the ability to extract this feature from data can be complicated by gaps in the EHT (u, v) coverage.",
    "It thus may not be directly related to any intrinsic A79, page 27 of 63",
    "The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024 image geometry (Tiede et al. 2022c).",
    "The depth of the central brightness depression and the fraction width measurements in 2018 are consistent with their respective measurements from 2017."
  ]
}